<h2 class="bold font-l">McBain and the Commie Nazis</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
The trope namer comes from an episode of The Simpsons, titled &quot;King Of The Hill&quot; where McBain is attacked by literal Commie Nazis while delivering UNICEF pennies to children. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="5ujc8y" data-video-descrip="The personification of Nazbol sings about how he is economically far left and socially far right, creating a totalitarian ideology combining what the audience sees as the worst aspects of the USSR and Nazi Germany, even though this would put him at odds with both regimes. " data-video-title="lil' nas(bol)" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/5ujc8y_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/5ujc8y.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/CommieNazis" data-video-tropename="Commie Nazis" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WebVideo/Jreg" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/5ujc8y.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">lil' nas(bol)</span></p>
</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="alt-titles section section-fact">
<h3>
<strong>Alternative Title(s):</strong>
<span>Nazi Commies</span>, <span>Communazi</span>, <span>Red Fascism</span> </h3>
</div>
